'''Bevier Memorial Building''' is a historic institutional building built originially for the [[Rochester Institute of Technology|Rochester Athaneaum and Mechanics Institute]] located at [[Rochester, New York|Rochester]] in [[Monroe County, New York]]. It is a three and a half brick story with ceramic trim designed by [[Claude Bragdon]] and completed in 1910.<ref name="nrhpinv_ny">{{cite web|url=http://www.oprhp.state.ny.us/hpimaging/hp_view.asp?GroupView=4175|title=National Register of Historic Places Registration: Bevier Memorial Building|date=August 1973|accessdate=2009-10-20 |author=Cornelia E. Brooke|publisher=[[New York State Office of Parks, Recreation and Historic Preservation]]}} ''See also:'' {{cite web|url=http://www.oprhp.state.ny.us/hpimaging/hp_view.asp?GroupView=4176|title=Accompanying photo}}</ref>

It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1973.<ref name="nris"/>

